were attempting to do precisely the opposite.
In spite of some misgivings about the failure to adapt the institutional
framework of the European Union to cater for 16 member states, which will
result in some MEPs abstaining or voting against enlargement, it was already
clear on Monday that most MEPs support the accession of Norway, Austria,
Finland and Sweden.
We will live to fight another day for the necessary institutional reforms,
notably in the 1996 Maastricht treaty revision.
