FT  05 MAY 94 / Call for new rules on car boot sales
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government should crack down on car boot sales, the Consumers'
Association said yesterday.
A report in its Which? magazine said it should be illegal for a trader to
operate at non-commercial car boot sales. It said commercial events should
be classed as markets and organisers required to register them with a local
authority.
Which? said new rules were needed to ensure that consumers' rights could be
enforced when they bought shoddy goods.
