FT  05 MAY 94 / Hyatt to run for US Senate seat
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEORGE GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Joel Hyatt, known across the US for his television advertisements on
behalf of his legal services retailing chain, has won the Democratic
nomination in the race to succeed his father-in-law, Senator Howard
Metzenbaum, as senator for Ohio.
The wealthy Mr Hyatt won a closely contested primary on Tuesday by 46 per
cent to 44 against a strong challenge from Ms Mary Boyle, a county
commissioner, who argued in her campaign that the Senate needed more
mothers, not more millionaires nor more lawyers.
In the November general election Mr Hyatt will face Mr Michael DeWine,
Ohio's Republican lieutenant governor, who won his party's primary with 52
per cent of the votes, defeating Dr Bernardine Healy, former director of the
National Institutes of Health.
In the same round of voting in Ohio, Congressman David Mann beat off a
challenge from Mr William Bowen, a state senator, for the Democratic
nomination in his House of Representatives district.
