FT  05 MAY 94 / Manifesto rebuff for Tory Euro-sceptics
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr John Major has rejected calls from the Tory right wing to recast in
Euro-sceptic terms the government's manifesto for the June 9 European
elections.
The near-final version of the document sticks with the careful compromises
set out in the original draft written by foreign secretary Douglas Hurd. The
draft marks a significant setback for the party's anti-Europeans.
The document has been shortened to give it a sharper edge and sections
attacking Labour and the Liberal Democrats have also been toughened up.
