<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexican losses reversed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexico
Stock prices reversed earlier losses to end firmer on a wave of technical
buying, analysts said.
The key IPC index of 36 top shares gained 8.5 points, a rise of 0.38 pe
rcent, to close at 2,239.23 after falling as low as 2,193.92 earlier in the
session.
Interest rates on benchmark 28-day treasury bills or Cetes were raised by 24
basis points to 16.49 per cent.
A flood of buy orders, the bulk of them for Telmex, came in shortly before
the closing bell. Some 36m shares of Telmex traded out of total turnover of
86.91m.
Telmex L shares, which may be held by foreigners, ended up 0.64 per cent
while the A shares ended unchanged.
Despite the positive finish, declining shares topped advancing shares 32 to
25.
Advancing issues were led by Bufete CPO series, rising 11.11 per cent, Dina,
up 5.88 per cent, Nadro L series, gaining 3.5 per cent, and Cemex CPO
shares, also up 3.5 per cent.
Venezuela
Shares on the Caracas stock exchange climbed strongly after the central bank
said that it was to hold an auction of dollars in an attempt to ease
pressure on the bolivar.
The Merinvest composite index rose 6.8 per cent to 112.39, recovering all of
Monday's losses. Electricidad de Caracas put on 34.50 bolivars to 310
bolivars.
