<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The euphoria surrounding South Africa's first all race elections propelled
Johannesburg higher last week, continuing a rising trend seen this year as
US funds have begun to flow into the market.
Analysts expect a measure of hesitancy in coming months as investors assess
the new cabinet and the government's first budget.
In the medium term, good economic growth prospects and a view that the ANC
will want to co-operate with business should prove positivefor the stock
market.
