<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / International Company News: Bavarian bank plans DM1bn rights
issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WALLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bayerische Hypotheken-und Wechsel-Bank, one of Germany's two big
Bavaria-based banks, is planning a one-for-10 rights issue. The terms will
be fixed around June 20 and the issue of 2.3m new shares is likely to raise
about DM1bn (Dollars 588m).
The bank, which recently reported a 33 per cent rise in pre-tax profits for
last year, said it needed the money in the context of strong business growth
last year and in the early months of the current year.
In the first two months of the year, Hypo-Bank's group operating profits
rose by 17 per cent, reflecting the bank's strong position in the buoyant
mortgage lending market.
The issue is the fourth from a leading German bank in the past six months.
The most recent was Dresdner Bank's innovative DM1.2bn equity placing with
international investors, details of which were announced last month. Of
Germany's biggest five banks, only Deutsche Bank, the largest, has said it
will not tap the equity market for the time being.
</TEXT>
