<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / UK Company News: BTR spins off Dartington
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER FRANKLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Crystal gazing - Mr Eric Dancer (left), managing director of Dartington
Crystal, and Mr Russ Cummings of 3i, reflect on the future of the giftware
and tableware producer which has been purchased by its management from BTR
in a Pounds 10m deal, writes Peter Franklin.
Under the terms of the transaction, which is backed by 3i, the venture
capital group, BTR's Rockware Group received Pounds 4.71m for the sale of
its 95 per cent holding as well as repayment of Pounds 3.25m in loans.
The Dartington Hall Trust, which founded the company in 1967 to create
employment in north Devon, has also sold its 5 per cent holding.
In addition, Dartington Crystal will receive Pounds 2m from the deal to fund
future growth plans.
Mr Cummings said that his company had led, structured and underwritten the
transaction, while Bank of Scotland was providing debt and working capital.
