FT  04 MAY 94 / Friendly society woos life company
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Family Assurance friendly society plans to buy Templeton Life Assurance,
part of the Templeton Marketing Group, for Pounds 1.75m. This is the first
time a friendly society has tried to acquire a life assurance company.
Templeton Life, which has Pounds 230m under management, markets and
underwrites life assurance and pension policies.
The acquisition on July 1 depends on Family Assurance members' agreement and
approval by the Friendly Societies' Commission.
