FT  04 MAY 94 / Boarding schools in funding talks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Boarding schools, which suffered a 5.2 per cent drop in boarding-pupil
numbers last year, are discussing possible extra state funds with education
ministers.
Mr Ian Small, chairman of the Boarding Schools Association, which represents
both independent and state boarding schools, and headmaster of Bootham
School in York, said: 'At the moment there are a lot of financial
constraints on parents.
He suggested that the government could contribute towards independent
schools' salary bills or it could expand the assisted places scheme, which
funds children from low-income families to attend independent schools.
