<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / Trade unionists protest government moves on pensions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Bill Morris, general secretary of the TGWU general union, and other trade
unionists gathered outside parliament yesterday with an 18ft inflatable
model of Robert Maxwell to protest at government moves over pensions.
Under a banner saying: 'Ministers - don't do a Maxwell on our pensions', the
union leaders, representing 1m members of the Local Government
Superannuation Scheme and 1m pensioners, claimed the moves threaten the
future of the scheme.
Mr Morris said: 'The government aim is to force increasing numbers out and
then break up the Local Government Superannuation Scheme. First the personal
pensions disaster and now this attack on the LGSS threaten poverty in old
age for a generation of pensioners in the 21st century'
