<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 94 / Eagle Trust action opens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eagle Trust, the film equipment conglomerate, yesterday began its High Court
action to recover Pounds 13.5m from Swiss Bank Corporation Investment
Banking.
Eagle Trust is suing Savory Milln, a stockbroking subsidiary of SBCI, over
its handling of the underwriting of the company's 1987 rights issue to fund
its takeover of Samuelson, a film equipment company. It claims the brokers
were reckless in accepting the Pounds 13.5m from Mr John Ferriday, Eagle
Trust's former chief executive, to meet his personal sub-underwriting
commitments to them.
Eagle Trust claims the money was misappropriated from the company by Mr
Ferriday to meet these sub-underwriting obligations and that Savory Milln
should have known this was the case. The case is expected to last three
weeks. Mr Ferriday was jailed for six years in April last year after being
convicted of six counts of theft from Eagle Trust to cover personal losses
sustained in the October 1987 stock market crash.
</TEXT>
